## User Story
As **Gabriel (Fleet Manager)**,
I want **a traffic-light indicator for km variance**,
So that **I can immediately see if balancing needs attention**.

## Acceptance Criteria

| AC | Criteria | Status |
|----|----------|--------|
| AC1 | Green indicator when variance ≤10% | PASS |
| AC2 | Yellow indicator when 10% < variance ≤20% | PASS |
| AC3 | Red indicator when variance >20% | PASS |
| AC4 | Icon changes with status (check/alert/x) | PASS |

## Implementation Details

### Files Modified
- `apps/web/src/components/dashboard/DashboardKPIs.tsx` - Added traffic light logic

### Traffic Light Logic
```typescript
const getVarianceStatus = (variance: number) => {
  if (variance <= 10) return { color: 'green', icon: CheckCircle };
  if (variance <= 20) return { color: 'yellow', icon: AlertTriangle };
  return { color: 'red', icon: XCircle };
};
```

### Visual Design
- Colored ring around variance KPI
- Lucide icons for status indication
- Animated pulse on red status

